<br>
<center>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Dojo floor repair 2023</span>
</center>
<br>
<br><br>

Because of wood rot, the middle third of the dojo flooring was recently replaced with fresh tongue-and-groove planks.<br><br>

The work was executed by MSCI Maintenance Department from July 27 - 30.<br><br>

<center>
<img src="photos/2023-Dojo-floor-repair1.jpg" style="padding:2px; margin:2px; border: 0px solid ; width: 641px; height: 854px;"  vspace="2"><br>

<img src="photos/2023-Dojo-floor-repair2.jpg" style="padding:2px; margin:2px; border: 0px solid ; width: 641px; height: 481px;"  vspace="2"><br><br>
</center>

Participants of the Wednesday class disassembled the jigsaw mats of our tatami on July 26th. On July 31st, with the new flooring in place, a small team of six members reassembled the mat structure. Many thanks to the members and guests who helped the mat disassembly and subsequent reassembly.<br><br>



<center>


 
<img src="photos/2023-Dojo-floor-repair3.jpg" style="padding:2px; margin:2px; border: 0px solid ; width: 641px; height: 481px;"  vspace="2"><br>
<img src="photos/2023-Dojo-floor-repair4.jpg" style="padding:2px; margin:2px; border: 0px solid ; width: 641px; height: 481px;"  vspace="2"><br>


</center>
